# gate.env — deliberately empty env file for the UI test gate.
#
# docker compose auto-loads tests/e2e-shell/.env (it sits in the project
# directory = the first -f file's dir). That file enables the AI scanner and
# carries Azure OpenAI credentials, which would make a developer's local gate
# render DIFFERENTLY from CI (CI has no .env): the dashboard shows AI-scanner
# status, so its visual baseline would flap between "AI enabled" locally and
# "AI disabled" in CI.
#
# Passing this file via `docker compose --env-file` suppresses the default .env
# load, so every AI_SCANNER_* interpolation falls back to its compose default
# (disabled / empty). The UI gate is then byte-for-byte reproducible between a
# dev laptop and CI, and no credentials ever reach it. Keep this file empty.
